edu.umd.cs.psl.config

Interface ConfigBundle

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    EmptyBundle

    public interface ConfigBundle
    Encapsulates a set of configuration properties organized by keys.

    • Method Detail

      • subset

        ConfigBundle subset(java.lang.String prefix)
        Return a ConfigBundle containing every key from the current ConfigBundle that starts with the specified prefix. The prefix is removed from the keys in the subset. For example, if the configuration contains the following properties: 
            prefix.number = 1
    prefix.string = Apache
    prefixed.foo = bar
    prefix = Jakarta
        the ConfigBundle returned by subset("prefix") will contain the properties: 
            number = 1
    string = Apache
    = Jakarta
        (The key for the value "Jakarta" is an empty string)
        Parameters:
        prefix - The prefix used to select the properties.
        Returns:
        a subset configuration bundle

      • addProperty

        void addProperty(java.lang.String key,
               java.lang.Object value)
        Add a property to the configuration. If it already exists then the value stated here will be added to the configuration entry. For example, if the property: 
         resource.loader = file
        is already present in the configuration and you call 
         addProperty("resource.loader", "classpath")
        Then you will end up with a List like the following: 
         ["file", "classpath"]
        Parameters:
        key - The key to add the property to.
        value - The value to add.

      • setProperty

        void setProperty(java.lang.String key,
               java.lang.Object value)
        Set a property, this will replace any previously set values. Set values is implicitly a call to clearProperty(key), addProperty(key, value).
        Parameters:
        key - The key of the property to change
        value - The new value

      • getBoolean

        boolean getBoolean(java.lang.String key,
                 boolean defaultValue)
        Get a boolean associated with the given configuration key. If the key doesn't map to an existing object, the default value is returned.
        Parameters:
        key - The configuration key.
        defaultValue - The default value.
        Returns:
        The associated boolean.
        Throws:
        ConversionException - is thrown if the key maps to an object that is not a Boolean.

      • getFactory

        Factory getFactory(java.lang.String key,
                 Factory defaultValue)
                   throws java.lang.ClassNotFoundException,
                          java.lang.IllegalAccessException,
                          java.lang.InstantiationException
        Gets a Factory associated with the given configuration key. If the value found is a String, then this method returns an instance of the class with that binary name.
        Parameters:
        key - The configuration key.
        defaultValue - The default value.
        Returns:
        The requested Factory if found, otherwise the default value.
        Throws:
        java.lang.ClassNotFoundException - The value found indicated a class that could not be found.
        java.lang.IllegalAccessException - The value found indicated a class that is not accessible.
        java.lang.InstantiationException - Instantiating the indicated class failed.

      • getEnum

        java.lang.Enum<?> getEnum(java.lang.String key,
                        java.lang.Enum<?> defaultValue)
        Returns an enum associated with the given configuration key. If the value found is a String, then it will be cast to an enum value of the same class as the default value.
        Parameters:
        key - The configuration key.
        defaultValue - The default value.
        Returns:
        The associated enum if the key is found, default value otherwise.
